00:09:51.000 --> 00:09:58.450
It recounts what happened to a
population called the Chagossians.

00:09:58.450 --> 00:10:01.320
They lived on islands, an
archipelago, the archipelago

00:10:01.320 --> 00:10:06.160
of Chagos which initially belonged
to the territory of Mauritius.

00:10:06.160 --> 00:10:08.240
Mauritisu, as you know,
is a small island state

00:10:08.240 --> 00:10:11.610
in the middle of the Indian Ocean.

00:10:11.610 --> 00:10:16.370
And we were formerly a British
colony from 1810 to 1968

00:10:16.370 --> 00:10:18.850
when we gained our independence.

00:10:18.850 --> 00:10:21.300
And when Mauritius asked
for its independence

00:10:21.300 --> 00:10:23.230
in the 1960's the British
said, "Okay.

00:10:23.230 --> 00:10:27.650 position:56%
We're going to give you independence
but we're just going to keep

00:10:27.650 --> 00:10:31.780
that part of your territory,
the Chagos archipelago."

00:10:31.780 --> 00:10:35.480
And there was a deal between
the British and the Americans

00:10:35.480 --> 00:10:41.970 position:56%
who wanted this particular place
and the main island that archipelago

00:10:41.970 --> 00:10:45.960
which is called Diego Garcia, they
wanted to establish a military base

00:10:45.960 --> 00:10:50.070
on this island because it was
ideally situated in the middle

00:10:50.070 --> 00:10:51.770
of the Indian Ocean to be able

00:10:51.770 --> 00:10:56.370
to control the whole
of the Middle East.

00:10:56.370 --> 00:11:00.030
And it must be known that
most of the bombings that went

00:11:00.030 --> 00:11:04.820
on these last years on
Afghanistan and Iraq killing

00:11:04.820 --> 00:11:07.840
from the island of Diego Garcia.

00:11:07.840 --> 00:11:11.720
So the United States said that
these islands are very important

00:11:11.720 --> 00:11:18.500
to maintain the security
of the "free" world.

00:11:18.500 --> 00:11:25.970 position:56%
But what is not really known is that
this freedom happened at the expense

00:11:25.970 --> 00:11:29.620
of the freedom of a population, the
Chagossians who were living there

00:11:29.620 --> 00:11:34.830
and who were disposed of
in terrible conditions.

00:11:34.830 --> 00:11:38.680
The British said to
the American that,

00:11:38.680 --> 00:11:41.810
first that there was no
[inaudible] on these islands.

00:11:41.810 --> 00:11:45.770
Then they had to get rid,
in a way, of these people

00:11:45.770 --> 00:11:50.060
and this happened in
two different phases.

00:11:50.060 --> 00:11:56.720
The first one, they tried to get
the people away by different means.

00:11:56.720 --> 00:11:58.020
They closed the hospital.

00:11:58.020 --> 00:12:05.490
They didn't send what we needed
for everyday life at first

00:12:05.490 --> 00:12:09.120
and they tried to get
them to go to Mauritius.

00:12:09.120 --> 00:12:15.050 position:56%
And when they wanted to take the
boat back to go back to the islands,

00:12:15.050 --> 00:12:17.810
they were told that
the islands were closed

00:12:17.810 --> 00:12:20.210
and that they weren't going back.

00:12:20.210 --> 00:12:25.570
And then the second phase in
the beginning of the, 1972,

00:12:25.570 --> 00:12:30.520
the Americans were getting
impatient so they just sent a boat.

00:12:30.520 --> 00:12:35.730
The people were given half an hour
to collect their things and get

00:12:35.730 --> 00:12:39.480
on the boat and go away without
being told what was happening

00:12:39.480 --> 00:12:41.890
to them, where they
were being taken.

00:12:41.890 --> 00:12:43.850
And they were thrown in Mauritius,

00:12:43.850 --> 00:12:47.890
totally helpless and
without anything.

00:12:47.890 --> 00:12:54.640
And these people have been fighting
for years for the recognition

00:12:54.640 --> 00:12:58.060
of the harm that has
been done to them.

00:12:58.060 --> 00:13:00.240
Mauritius has been
fighting also as a state

00:13:00.240 --> 00:13:03.890
to claim sovereignty
on that [inaudible].

00:13:03.890 --> 00:13:06.290
And three weeks back
our Prime Minister was

00:13:06.290 --> 00:13:10.360
at the National Assembly of
the United Nations in New York

00:13:10.360 --> 00:13:16.660
to reaffirm our claim on these
islands and this is a story

00:13:16.660 --> 00:13:23.240 position:56%
that struck me, not for its
geopolitical and historical context,

00:13:23.240 --> 00:13:25.180
but for the people
who were concerned.

00:13:25.180 --> 00:13:28.990
And I met some of these people.

00:13:28.990 --> 00:13:35.940
They confided their story to me and
I really wanted to get it across,

00:13:35.940 --> 00:13:41.480
